collections.name: Living Room Extravaganza II
collections.description:
Living Room Extravaganza II by Harman is a daring exploration of AI-driven artworks, built on the foundation of their original postpaintings. These works blur the lines between human expression and digital experimentation, juxtaposing serene domestic interiors with hints of chaos looming just outside. 

Dreamlike and abstract, the series captures the tension between comfort and turmoil, reflecting the fragility of modern life. Pulsing with spontaneous energy yet meticulously composed, Living Room Extravaganza II challenges viewers to confront the dissonance between interior sanctuaries and the turbulence beyond, marking Harman as a visionary in the evolving AI and postpainting landscape.

collections.name: Conway's Game Of Life
collections.description: Conway's Game of Life is a cellular automaton where players set up an initial pattern of "live" cells on a grid, and the cells evolve over time based on simple rules, with each cell's state depending on the state of its neighboring cells, resulting in complex patterns and behaviors emerging from these basic rules, even though the game itself has no direct player input beyond the initial configuration; essentially, it's a simulation of life-like behavior on a grid where cells can be either "alive" or "dead" and their status changes based on the number of live neighbors they have.

collections.name: Celestial Graph
collections.description:
Where does your time flow?

For centuries, humans have read time through the stars, defining their place in the universe. Celestial Graph extends this journey, transforming real-time constellation data into art. By mapping celestial coordinates down to precise moments, it captures time's passage and cosmic wonder.

Recorded every 12 minutes, 120 movements symbolize time's relativity. Each star maps its own pace — from Polaris’s steady glow to fleeting comets. Celestial Graph weaves these rhythms into your personal timeline.

Colors are derived from light wavelengths at constellations’ peak altitude, with metadata preserved on Arweave’s Permaweb, forever connecting your story to the universe.

collections.name: Ingex Standard
collections.description:
With the Ingex Genesis set sold out, the Standard set is our long-planned second and final allocation. 

Like Genesis tokens, they will provide governance rights and a revenue share, albeit at a lower yield than the former, upon the official launch of the Ingex zk-oracle.

Only a couple of dozen tokens will be part of the Standard set. 

Ingex is a next-generation oracle that leverages zero-knowledge proofs for greater security and cost-effectiveness than existing optimistic oracles.

The team consists of early pioneers in the ZK space, previously making contributions to the first iteration of zk-rollups that now provides the infrastructure for countless dapps.
